DataElement.preferredName: Surgical Procedure Fine-Needle Aspiration Core Biopsy Performed Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the date of the most recent an operative procedure performed that removes tissue or fluid with a relatively small needle for examination under a microscope or that removes a tissue sample using a needle with a relatively large diameter, for microscopic examination.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Surgical Procedure Fine-Needle Aspiration Core Biopsy Performed
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to an operative procedure being performed that removes tissue or fluid with a relatively small needle for examination under a microscope or that removes a tissue sample using a needle with a relatively large diameter, for microscopic examination.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Used for operative procedures on organs, regions, or tissues in the treatment of diseases, including tissue section by lasers. It excludes transplantation, for which "transplantation" is used.

Concepts.definition: A diagnostic or treatment procedure performed by manual and/or instrumental means, often involving an incision and the removal or replacement of a diseased organ or tissue; of or relating to or involving or used in surgery or requiring or amenable to treatment by surgery.

Property.preferredDefinition: The removal of tissue or fluid with a needle for examination under a microscope. Also called needle biopsy.:The removal of a tissue sample using a needle with a relatively large diameter, for microscopic examination.:Performed; carried out.

Concepts.definition: The removal of tissue or fluid with a thin needle for examination under a microscope.
The removal of a tissue sample using a needle with a relatively large diameter, for microscopic examination.
Executed and carried through to completion.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: actions or administration of therapeutic agents to produce an effect that is intended to alter the course of a pathologic process (NCI).

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: the most recent date of an event, assessment, or treatment.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: Nearest to the present time.:a particular day specified as the time something has, or will, happen.

Concepts.definition: The particular day, month and year an event has happened or will happen.
